  <!-- OVERVIEW -->
  <section id="overview">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-num">00</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Overview</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="abstract-box">
      <p>
        This project builds and evaluates a full credit card approval prediction pipeline on a real-world
        applicant dataset. We conduct thorough exploratory data analysis, apply principled feature
        engineering (credit score binning via decision trees, log-income transformation, interaction terms),
        and benchmark <strong>six classifier families</strong> using a cross-validated F-beta evaluation
        framework that prioritizes recall — reflecting the business cost of incorrectly rejecting qualified
        applicants. The analysis concludes with a <strong>demographic bias audit</strong> examining approval
        disparities across ethnicity groups and employment sectors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-number green">6</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">Classifier families<br />benchmarked</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-number">β = 2</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">F-beta objective<br />(recall-weighted)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-cell">
        <div class="stat-number blue">4</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">Credit score bins<br />(decision-tree split)</div>
      </div>
